title: Grateful Dead Live at Portland Memorial Coliseum on 1980-06-12
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition CC2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Peggy-O-> El Paso, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, Far From Me, Althea-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Drums-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
SBD! Its nice seeing a SBD of this show. My friend saw this and Spokane that ashy tour. It gives hope that more boards are out there for shows still without. Its a relief to hear this as a board. Nice recording IMHO everyone is represented well.
Unremarkable first set, although i do love BEW, tonight is not the night, a lackluster compare to earlier years IMHO.Althea was played heavy 80-81 nice to hear Jers voice clear and articulate.
A funky Fire On The Mountain with Jerry playing fiercely made up for vocal flubs and a solid Estimated are keepers for the second set. Bring on more boards!
